cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper proposes a method for solving large scale non-convex optimization problems in neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions benchmark classification and regression problems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of Tensorflow suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with optimization, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
